        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/billie80/{size}/1331_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-31T11:54:29.565Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Note this describes the situation on Android, I do not know the workflow on iOS.</p>\n<p>By browsing around here I accidentally found that it is possible to send messages (containing images) to multiple recipients at once (<a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/wiki-feature-comparison-android-ios-desktop/12003\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Feature Comparison: Android, iOS, Desktop</a>). Up to now I was always composing the message, send it to the first contact and then forward it to the next.</p>\n<p>By looking at other posts it seems that this feature is not common knowledge as it is not documented (<a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/wiki-features-and-abilities-which-are-not-documented-in-app/12045\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Features and abilities which are not documented in-app</a>).</p>\n<p>Other topics also show that there is a demand and that the current workflow is not easy to discover:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/send-signal-messages-sms-mms-to-multiple-recipients/222\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Send Signal messages to multiple recipients</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/allow-sharing-a-link-or-media-with-multiple-recipients-users-at-the-same-time/5794\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Allow sharing a link or media with multiple recipients/users at the same time</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/forward-a-message-media-file-to-multiple-contacts/5888\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Forward a message/media/file to multiple contacts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/sending-a-message-to-multiple-users/6568\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Sending a message to multiple users</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/how-do-i-send-to-multiple-addressees/13204\" class=\"inline-onebox\">How Do I Send To Multiple Addressees?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/privacy-more-control-over-who-can-see-my-profile-photo/12101/11\" class=\"inline-onebox\">More control over who can see my profile photo - #11 by th7803</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also the current solution is not really intuitive and requires many steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click the camera button on the main screen</li>\n<li>Instead of taking a picture go to the gallery by clicking the bottom-left floating button</li>\n<li>Select at least one picture</li>\n<li>Accept the selected picture(s) by clicking the blue  bottom-right button with the image count</li>\n<li>Compose message</li>\n<li>Click blue bottom-right arrow</li>\n<li>Select recipients</li>\n<li>Finally send the message</li>\n</ol>\n<p>It is also not possible to use this as a workaround to only send text, because after you remove the selected image you are thrown back to the main screen.</p>\n<p>I am not sure what is the best way to improve it but the following came to mind.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click the blue compose message button</li>\n<li>Allow the selection of multiple recipients from the contact list (long click the first contact then select additional contacts)</li>\n<li>Accept selection</li>\n<li>Compose message</li>\n<li>Send message</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The order of this workflow is reversed as here the recipients are selected before composing the message but I don’t think this is a big issue. Also it would allow to send text only messages to multiple recipients.</p>\n<p>I think all that is needed is a revamping of the UI as everything needed seems to exist already.</p>\n<p>What do you think?</p>",
