        "created_at": "2020-05-31T12:25:08.785Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It is actually conveignient to be able to choose other recipients after you wrote the message, otherwise if you change youinf you would have to discard you message or safe it as draft just to go back and change which receipients you want to send to. So for that reason a reversed workflow might mot be the best.</p>\n<p>There are already feature requests to send messages to multiple receipients. With many variations on them</p>\n<ul>\n<li>just sending to multiple receipients one time</li>\n<li>creating a list of reciepients to whom you can send multiple times</li>\n<li>creating a one way group to whom you can broadcast messages but they can’t reply</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I don’t see what this feature request is about. Don’t the otherfeature request already cover this?</p>\n<p>You also linked to a topic I wrote about forwarding multiple messages, but forwarding is not the same as writing a new message, thus that is an unrealted feature request. I see how it would help asawork around though.</p>",
