        "id": 66674,
        "name": "Daniel Pielmeier",
        "username": "billie80",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/billie80/{size}/1331_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-31T12:54:26.879Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Meteor0id\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14596\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/meteor0id/48/55420_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Meteor0id:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It is actually conveignient to be able to choose other recipients after you wrote the message, otherwise if you change youinf you would have to discard you message or safe it as draft just to go back and change which receipients you want to send to. So for that reason a reversed workflow might mot be the best.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I get your point!</p>\n<p>Then we need a method to start message composition independent of the existing and the proposed workflow where one gets to the compose part first. As I said I am not sure if it is the best way of implementing it.</p>\n<p>On the other hand we just need to be able to save all kind of drafts not just text messages (<a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/drafts-are-not-saved-anymore-with-the-new-media-send-flow/7204\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Drafts are not saved anymore with the new media send flow</a>) <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/grinning.png?v=14\" title=\":grinning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":grinning:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Meteor0id\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14596\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/meteor0id/48/55420_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Meteor0id:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There are already feature requests to send messages to multiple receipients. With many variations on them</p>\n<ul>\n<li>just sending to multiple receipients one time</li>\n<li>creating a list of reciepients to whom you can send multiple times</li>\n<li>creating a one way group to whom you can broadcast messages but they can’t reply</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I don’t see what this feature request is about. Don’t the otherfeature request already cover this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I know but this are feature requests about the implementation of sending to multiple recipients. However the feature already exists just in a non intuitive way. So this is about making it more intuitive. Done properly this could also cover some of the other requested variations.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Meteor0id\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"14596\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/meteor0id/48/55420_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Meteor0id:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You also linked to a topic I wrote about forwarding multiple messages, but forwarding is not the same as writing a new message, thus that is an unrealted feature request. I see how it would help asawork around though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>You are right it is not the same. I somehow misread this as in forwarding a message to multiple recipients. This would be unnecessary in most cases if we can send to multiple recipients to begin with. I will remove it from the list.</p>",
