        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/edb3f5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-06-20T13:10:13.195Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I would be very happy if Signal would create the possibillity to select multiple users/contacts to send a message <strong>without creating a group</strong>.</p>\n<p>Incidentally I have to send a message to multiple users. Now I have to create a group, send the message en then delete the group again. If I delete the group, all messages are lost for me.</p>\n<p>Whatsapp has an option to create a one-time list of recipiens and send them a message. These messages are then stored in the message lists of all individual users.</p>",
