        "created_at": "2025-06-20T17:22:33.978Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This sounds like something that falls under this request:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"4798\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/theboatman/48/1087_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/infogroups-channels-broadcast-lists/4798\">InfoGroups / Channels / Broadcast lists</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I am missing the possibility to create groups where only the creator can see the members and post to that group, for sending out information about events or something like that. That would be useful if you have a larger group of people to inform who do not know each other or at least are not very close to each other. \nThis could be a teacher informing his students, or a medical practice, basically any event where you know the main person/organisation but not the other participants. \nI think this…\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
